#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.139"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.139:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.139:0.2"
msgid "14. Puggalavagga "
msgstr "14. Persons "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.139:0.3"
msgid "139. Dhammakathikasutta "
msgstr "139. Dhamma Speakers "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.139:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, dhammakathikā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four Dhamma speakers. "

msgctxt "an4.139:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.139:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco dhammakathiko appañca bhāsati asahitañca; "
msgstr "One Dhamma speaker speaks little and off topic. "

#. VAR: parisā cassa → parisā ca (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.139:1.4"
msgid "parisā cassa na kusalā hoti sahitāsahitassa. "
msgstr "And their assembly can’t tell what’s on topic and what’s off topic. "

msgctxt "an4.139:1.5"
msgid "Evarūpo, bhikkhave, dhammakathiko evarūpāya parisāya dhammakathikotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "Such an assembly regards such a Dhamma speaker simply as a Dhamma speaker. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.139:2.1"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco dhammakathiko appañca bhāsati sahitañca; "
msgstr "One Dhamma speaker speaks little but stays on topic. "

msgctxt "an4.139:2.2"
msgid "parisā cassa kusalā hoti sahitāsahitassa. "
msgstr "And their assembly can tell what’s on topic and what’s off topic. "

msgctxt "an4.139:2.3"
msgid "Evarūpo, bhikkhave, dhammakathiko evarūpāya parisāya dhammakathikotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "Such an assembly regards such a Dhamma speaker simply as a Dhamma speaker. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.139:3.1"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco dhammakathiko bahuñca bhāsati asahitañca; "
msgstr "One Dhamma speaker speaks much but off topic. "

msgctxt "an4.139:3.2"
msgid "parisā cassa na kusalā hoti sahitāsahitassa. "
msgstr "And their assembly can’t tell what’s on topic and what’s off topic. "

msgctxt "an4.139:3.3"
msgid "Evarūpo, bhikkhave, dhammakathiko evarūpāya parisāya dhammakathikotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "Such an assembly regards such a Dhamma speaker simply as a Dhamma speaker. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.139:4.1"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco dhammakathiko bahuñca bhāsati sahitañca; "
msgstr "One Dhamma speaker speaks much and stays on topic. "

msgctxt "an4.139:4.2"
msgid "parisā cassa kusalā hoti sahitāsahitassa. "
msgstr "And their assembly can tell what’s on topic and what’s off topic. "

msgctxt "an4.139:4.3"
msgid "Evarūpo, bhikkhave, dhammakathiko evarūpāya parisāya dhammakathikotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "Such an assembly regards such a Dhamma speaker simply as a Dhamma speaker. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.139:4.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro dhammakathikā”ti. "
msgstr "These are the four Dhamma speakers.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.139:4.5"
msgid "Navamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
